        <h2>Why Healthcare Workers Get Priority</h2>
        <p>
          British Columbia is experiencing a <strong
            >critical healthcare worker shortage</strong
          >. Hospitals throughout the province urgently need nurses, physicians,
          and allied health professionals. This shortage has made the Health
          Authority stream one of the most favorable pathways in BC PNP. Beyond public health authorities, BC also has separate priority pathways for <a href="/articles/bc-pnp-caregivers-childcare" class="text-sky-600 hover:underline">Early Childhood Educators (ECEs) and Caregivers</a>.
        </p>

        <h3>Key Advantages</h3>
        <ul class="marker:text-sky-600">
